After adding the functionalities of your upload button, let's start coding for
our DOWNLOAD button.

From the previous guide
[http://blog.proximax.io/coding-your-first-application-upload], we have
populated our combo box with names of the files we uploaded. Now we will select
a file from that combo box, download it from the network and save it locally.

Let's start initializing the download service, by passing it through a 
PeerConnection  (We used Remote Peer Connection from our previous guide.)

Download download = new Download(remotePeerConnection);


Just like the upload service, the download also requires a download parameter
containing the NEM Hash. But since we only have file names listed on our combo
box, we will be searching for the file first using ProximaX searchByName 
function. To do that, add in the following code:

//should search for the file using name
Search search = new Search(remotePeerConnection);
final List<ResourceHashMessageJsonEntity> result = search.searchByName(TEST_PRIVATE_KEY, TEST_PUBLIC_KEY, cboFiles.getSelectedItem().toString());
String hashForDownload = result.get(0).getNemHash().toString();


Now that we have searched for the file, we can get the NEM Hash and use it on
our download parameter.

//should download file
final DownloadFileResult downloadFileResult = download.downloadFile(DownloadParameter.create().nemHash(hashForDownload).build());
